cs.DB, cs.PL, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.CR 

The paper deals with provenance, which is a concept closely related to databases and data management. Therefore, cs.DB is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents extensions to the Links programming language, which is a programming language that focuses on web applications and has features related to query and data manipulation. This makes cs.PL and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the safety and efficiency of the proposed approach, which are topics related to software engineering (cs.SE) and cryptography (cs.CR).
